From: Si-Wei Liu <si-wei.liu@oracle.com>
Date: Mon, 21 Oct 2024 16:40:40 +0300
Subject: vdpa/mlx5: Fix suboptimal range on iotlb iteration
Patch-mainline: v6.13-rc1
Git-commit: 35025963326e44d8bced3eecd42d2f040f4f0024
References: git-fixes

The starting iova address to iterate iotlb map entry within a range
was set to an irrelevant value when passing to the itree_next()
iterator, although luckily it doesn't affect the outcome of finding
out the granule of the smallest iotlb map size. Fix the code to make
it consistent with the following for-loop.

Fixes: 94abbccdf291 ("vdpa/mlx5: Add shared memory registration code")
Signed-off-by: Si-Wei Liu <si-wei.liu@oracle.com>
Signed-off-by: Dragos Tatulea <dtatulea@nvidia.com>
Message-Id: <20241021134040.975221-3-dtatulea@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Michael S. Tsirkin <mst@redhat.com>
Acked-by: Jason Wang <jasowang@redhat.com>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/vdpa/mlx5/core/mr.c |    4 +---
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/vdpa/mlx5/core/mr.c
+++ b/drivers/vdpa/mlx5/core/mr.c
@@ -227,7 +227,6 @@ static int map_direct_mr(struct mlx5_vdp
 	unsigned long lgcd = 0;
 	int log_entity_size;
 	unsigned long size;
-	u64 start = 0;
 	int err;
 	struct page *pg;
 	unsigned int nsg;
@@ -238,10 +237,9 @@ static int map_direct_mr(struct mlx5_vdp
 	struct device *dma = mvdev->vdev.dma_dev;
 
 	for (map = vhost_iotlb_itree_first(iotlb, mr->start, mr->end - 1);
-	     map; map = vhost_iotlb_itree_next(map, start, mr->end - 1)) {
+	     map; map = vhost_iotlb_itree_next(map, mr->start, mr->end - 1)) {
 		size = maplen(map, mr);
 		lgcd = gcd(lgcd, size);
-		start += size;
 	}
 	log_entity_size = ilog2(lgcd);
 
